   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Custom Resume Entity Extractor\\n\",\"**NLP Project 22 of 100** — Extract skills, roles, education, and experience from resume text using spaCy NER and custom patterns.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Use spaCy's EntityRuler for custom entity patterns.\\n\",\"2. Combine rule-based and ML-based NER.\\n\",\"3. Extract structured data from semi-structured resumes.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in ['pandas','numpy','spacy']:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\ntry: import spacy; spacy.load('en_core_web_sm')\\nexcept: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','spacy','download','en_core_web_sm'])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, re, spacy\\nfrom spacy.tokens import Span\\nnlp = spacy.load('en_core_web_sm')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Add custom entity patterns\\nruler = nlp.add_pipe('entity_ruler', before='ner')\\npatterns = [\\n    {'label':'SKILL','pattern':p} for p in\\n    ['Python','Java','JavaScript','React','Docker','Kubernetes','AWS','GCP','Azure',\\n     'TensorFlow','PyTorch','SQL','MongoDB','PostgreSQL','FastAPI','Flask','Git',\\n     'machine learning','deep learning','NLP','computer vision','data science']\\n] + [\\n    {'label':'DEGREE','pattern':p} for p in\\n    ['BS','MS','PhD','Bachelor','Master','MBA','B.S.','M.S.','Ph.D.']\\n] + [\\n    {'label':'ROLE','pattern':p} for p in\\n    ['Software Engineer','Data Scientist','ML Engineer','Product Manager',\\n     'Senior Developer','Tech Lead','CTO','VP Engineering']\\n]\\nruler.add_patterns(patterns)\\nprint(f'Added {len(patterns)} patterns.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"SAMPLE_RESUME = \\\"\\\"\\\"John Smith\\nSenior Software Engineer at Google\\nMS Computer Science, Stanford University\\n\\nExperience:\\n- Built ML pipelines using Python, TensorFlow, and Docker\\n- Led team of 5 engineers deploying models on AWS and Kubernetes\\n- Implemented NLP solutions for customer support automation\\n\\nSkills: Python, Java, TensorFlow, PyTorch, Docker, AWS, SQL, Git\\nEducation: MS Computer Science, Stanford University, 2018\\n           BS Mathematics, MIT, 2016\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\ndoc = nlp(SAMPLE_RESUME)\\nprint('Extracted Entities:')\\nfor ent in doc.ents:\\n    print(f'  {ent.label_:10s} {ent.text}')\\n\\n# Group by type\\nfrom collections import defaultdict\\nextracted = defaultdict(set)\\nfor ent in doc.ents:\\n    extracted[ent.label_].add(ent.text)\\n\\nprint('\\\\nStructured Output:')\\nfor label, values in sorted(extracted.items()):\\n    print(f'  {label}: {sorted(values)}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **spaCy EntityRuler + NER provides robust entity extraction** from resumes.\\n\",\"- **Custom patterns catch domain-specific entities** (skills, degrees) that general NER misses.\\n\",\"- **For production, train a custom spaCy NER model** on labeled resume data.\\n\",\"- **Output can feed into ATS systems** for automated candidate screening.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
